\begin_layout Standard
This mechanism has also been attributed to the occurrence of heatwaves (citation
s).
 However, Reeder et at.
 (2015) argue that fire weather and heatwave conditions are usually different.
 This study only mentions that cold fronts are the defining feature of fire
 weather.
 Other studies also mention that fire and heatwaves are related events without
 providing further details (citations).
 It would be interesting to explore the differences between these two types
 of events.
 Our ability to predict these events could benefit from an understanding
 of the characteristics that distinguish them.
 The interactions between them also remain unexplored.
 Therefore, to investigate this relationship, it is also important to review
 the heatwave literature.
\end_layout

